 {"id":"franken_networkx-zzcm7","title":"[HIGH] REVIEW: directed component and topological error contracts diverge","description":"The wide parity matrix found strongly_connected_components yields SCCs in a different order from upstream NetworkX on directed fixtures. It also found topological_sort on a cyclic digraph raises HasACycle where upstream raises NetworkXUnfeasible.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-24T00:56:26.319497097Z","created_by":"codex","updated_at":"2026-04-24T00:56:26.319497097Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"franken_networkx-zzcm8","title":"[HIGH] REVIEW: local_bridges graph-family rejection contracts diverge","description":"The wide parity matrix found local_bridges returns results on directed graphs and MultiGraph inputs where upstream NetworkX raises NetworkXNotImplemented.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-24T00:56:26.319497097Z","created_by":"codex","updated_at":"2026-04-24T00:56:26.319497097Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"franken_networkx-zzcm9","title":"[HIGH] REVIEW: MultiGraph structural algorithms diverge from NetworkX","description":"The wide parity matrix found MultiGraph-specific structural gaps: is_tree and is_forest return true despite parallel edges where upstream returns false; bridges includes the parallel edge pair that upstream excludes; degree_centrality undercounts parallel-edge degree; complement raises TypeError where upstream returns a MultiGraph complement.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-24T00:56:26.319497097Z","created_by":"codex","updated_at":"2026-04-24T00:56:26.319497097Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
-{"id": "franken_networkx-grid2d", "title": "REVIEW: [HIGH] grid_2d_graph node type is str instead of tuple", "description": "fnx.grid_2d_graph(m, n) delegates to Rust fast path when create_using is None and m/n are ints. Rust emits node labels as strings like \"0,0\" whereas nx uses tuples (0,0). Breaks drop-in: G[(0,0)] raises KeyError on fnx. Python fallback is already correct. Fix: bypass Rust fast path.", "status": "open", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T03:42:56.094028Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T03:42:56.094028Z", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0}
-{"id": "franken_networkx-hypcub", "title": "REVIEW: [HIGH] hypercube_graph node type is int instead of tuple of bits", "description": "fnx re-exports hypercube_graph directly from Rust. nx.hypercube_graph(n) returns nodes labeled as tuples of n 0/1 ints (e.g. (0,0,0)); fnx returns integer labels 0..2^n-1. Breaks drop-in: G[(0,0,0)] raises KeyError. Fix: Python wrapper matching nx.", "status": "open", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T03:42:56.094028Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T03:42:56.094028Z", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0}
-{"id": "franken_networkx-kneser", "title": "REVIEW: [HIGH] kneser_graph node type is str instead of tuple", "description": "fnx.kneser_graph(n, k) produces nodes labeled as strings like \"0,1\". nx.kneser_graph produces tuple nodes (0,1). Breaks drop-in: user code indexing by tuple fails. Fix: Python wrapper or relabel.", "status": "open", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T03:42:56.094028Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T03:42:56.094028Z", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0}
-{"id": "franken_networkx-turan5", "title": "REVIEW: [MEDIUM] turan_graph produces different node labels than networkx", "description": "fnx.turan_graph(n, r) produces the complete r-partite graph with different partition node assignment than nx. Both are isomorphic (same graph class), but specific edges differ (e.g., for (5,2) nx has (0,2) but fnx has (0,1)). User code comparing specific edges diverges. Fix: rewrite Python wrapper to match nx turan_graph node partition order.", "status": "open", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T03:42:56.094028Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T03:42:56.094028Z", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0}
-{"id": "franken_networkx-anftup", "title": "REVIEW: [HIGH] add_nodes_from treats hashable 2-tuples as (node, attrs) and silently drops the 2nd element", "description": "fnx.Graph().add_nodes_from([(0,1),(0,2),(1,2)]) adds nodes [0,1] instead of the three tuple nodes. The Rust-level add_nodes_from unconditionally unpacks 2-tuples as (node, attrs) even when the tuple is hashable (second element not a dict). nx dispatches via hashability: hashable tuple -> node label; unhashable (dict in 2nd slot) -> (node, attrs). Breaks drop-in for any code that uses tuple-labeled nodes via add_nodes_from \u2014 grid_2d_graph / kneser_graph / hypercube_graph / geometric graphs all hit this. 3-tuples and longer are unaffected because Rust only special-cases length-2. Fix: Python-level wrapper on Graph/DiGraph/MultiGraph/MultiDiGraph matching nx hash-based dispatch.", "status": "open", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T03:46:50.118934Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T03:46:50.118934Z", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0}
-{"id": "franken_networkx-updatg", "title": "REVIEW: [HIGH] Graph.update(H) crashes when H is a Graph instance instead of edge-bunch", "description": "fnx.Graph.update (Rust-native) treats its first positional arg as an edge iterable unconditionally. nx.Graph.update duck-types: if the arg has .nodes and .edges attributes, treat it as a Graph and copy nodes+edges+graph-level attrs; otherwise treat as an edge bunch. Result: fnx.Graph().update(nx_or_fnx_Graph) raises TypeError: each edge must be a tuple (u, v) or (u, v, attr_dict). Fixed via Python-level wrapper that matches nx duck-typing. Caught via add_nodes_from adjacent-find.", "status": "open", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T03:48:15.451238Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T03:48:15.451238Z", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0}
