+{"id": "franken_networkx-hypcub", "title": "REVIEW: [HIGH] hypercube_graph node type is int instead of tuple of bits", "description": "fnx re-exports hypercube_graph directly from Rust. nx.hypercube_graph(n) returns nodes labeled as tuples of n 0/1 ints (e.g. (0,0,0)); fnx returns integer labels 0..2^n-1. Breaks drop-in: G[(0,0,0)] raises KeyError. Fix: Python wrapper matching nx.", "status": "closed", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T03:42:56.094028Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T04:34:16.823011Z", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0, "closed_at": "2026-04-24T04:34:16.823011Z", "close_reason": "Fixed in 923177e: hypercube_graph Python wrapper emits bit tuples"}
