 {"id": "franken_networkx-keystr", "title": "REVIEW: [MEDIUM] KeyError on missing graph key stringifies the key (str, not int/tuple/native)", "description": "Every __getitem__ on a fnx graph view (G[n], G.adj[n], G.nodes[n]) raises KeyError(str(key)) on miss, instead of KeyError(key) with the original type. Result: repr(e.args[0]) for fnx diverges from nx. Examples: G[99] -> KeyError(\"99\"); G[\"xx\"] -> KeyError(\"'xx'\") (repr of string, including quotes); G[(99,99)] -> KeyError(\"(99, 99)\"). Breaks typed except handlers that compare e.args[0] to the queried key. Likely fixed on the Rust PyO3 side (format!(\"{}\", key) used in map.get path; should be map.get(&key).ok_or_else(|| PyKeyError::new_err(key.clone()))). Also affects string reprs in error messages.", "status": "open", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T04:02:35.778354Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T04:02:35.778354Z", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0}
-{"id": "franken_networkx-wredge", "title": "REVIEW: [HIGH] write_edgelist output format is incompatible with nx.read_edgelist", "description": "fnx.write_edgelist emits \"u v -\" for empty attr dicts and \"u v key=val\" when attrs present, instead of nx's \"u v {}\" / \"u v {'key': val}\" Python-dict repr. Result: fnx-written files fail to round-trip through nx.read_edgelist with TypeError: Failed to convert edge data ([\"-\"]) to dictionary. Also missing trailing newline. The Rust-native write_edgelist does not accept data/comments/delimiter/encoding kwargs that nx has. Fix via Python wrapper that delegates the format to nx under a private helper.", "status": "open", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T04:11:47.343593Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T04:11:47.343593Z", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0}
-{"id": "franken_networkx-rdedge", "title": "REVIEW: [MEDIUM] read_edgelist signature missing nodetype/create_using/data/delimiter/comments/encoding kwargs", "description": "fnx.read_edgelist(path) only accepts path. nx.read_edgelist has (path, comments, delimiter, create_using, nodetype, data, edgetype, encoding). Users calling nx-compatible forms like fnx.read_edgelist(path, nodetype=int) get TypeError. Similarly read_adjlist is missing these kwargs.", "status": "open", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T04:11:47.343593Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T04:11:47.343593Z", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0}
+{"id": "franken_networkx-wredge", "title": "REVIEW: [HIGH] write_edgelist output format is incompatible with nx.read_edgelist", "description": "fnx.write_edgelist emits \"u v -\" for empty attr dicts and \"u v key=val\" when attrs present, instead of nx's \"u v {}\" / \"u v {'key': val}\" Python-dict repr. Result: fnx-written files fail to round-trip through nx.read_edgelist with TypeError: Failed to convert edge data ([\"-\"]) to dictionary. Also missing trailing newline. The Rust-native write_edgelist does not accept data/comments/delimiter/encoding kwargs that nx has. Fix via Python wrapper that delegates the format to nx under a private helper.", "status": "closed", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T04:11:47.343593Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T04:34:16.823011Z", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0, "closed_at": "2026-04-24T04:34:16.823011Z", "close_reason": "Fixed in 15a3382: write_edgelist delegates via private helper to nx format"}
+{"id": "franken_networkx-rdedge", "title": "REVIEW: [MEDIUM] read_edgelist signature missing nodetype/create_using/data/delimiter/comments/encoding kwargs", "description": "fnx.read_edgelist(path) only accepts path. nx.read_edgelist has (path, comments, delimiter, create_using, nodetype, data, edgetype, encoding). Users calling nx-compatible forms like fnx.read_edgelist(path, nodetype=int) get TypeError. Similarly read_adjlist is missing these kwargs.", "status": "closed", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T04:11:47.343593Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T04:34:16.823011Z", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0, "closed_at": "2026-04-24T04:34:16.823011Z", "close_reason": "Fixed in 15a3382: read_edgelist/read_adjlist honour nodetype/create_using/etc."}
 {"id": "franken_networkx-wadjlk", "title": "REVIEW: [MEDIUM] write_adjlist signature advertises kwargs it runtime-rejects", "description": "fnx.write_adjlist has signature (g, path, comments=\"#\", delimiter=\" \", encoding=\"utf-8\") matching nx, but passing any non-default kwarg raises NetworkXNotImplemented: franken_networkx currently only supports default parameters for write_adjlist. The signature is misleading. Either implement the kwargs honestly or remove them from the signature and raise TypeError on any non-default value.", "status": "open", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T04:11:47.343593Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T04:11:47.343593Z", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0}
 {"id": "franken_networkx-grphml", "title": "REVIEW: [MEDIUM] write_graphml refuses MultiGraph; read_graphml missing node_type/force_multigraph kwargs", "description": "fnx.write_graphml(MG) raises TypeError: write_graphml does not support MultiGraph or MultiDiGraph without losing parallel edges. nx.write_graphml handles MultiGraph via edge-key emission. fnx.read_graphml also drops node_type, edge_key_type, force_multigraph kwargs that nx accepts. Consider Python-side delegation for MultiGraph write + kwarg forwarding on read.", "status": "open", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T04:11:47.343593Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T04:11:47.343593Z", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0}
 {"id": "franken_networkx-wgmldr", "title": "REVIEW: [LOW] write_gml always emits \"directed 0\" even for undirected graphs", "description": "fnx.write_gml(Graph()) produces \"graph [\n  directed 0\n]\n\" but nx.write_gml produces \"graph [\n]\n\" (omits the directed field for undirected graphs). Both are readable by nx.read_gml, but the byte-level divergence surprises users comparing outputs. Low priority.", "status": "open", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T04:11:47.343593Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T04:11:47.343593Z", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0}
-{"id": "franken_networkx-xmginit", "title": "REVIEW: [HIGH] cross-class constructor drops edges \u2014 fnx.Graph(MultiGraph) returns empty", "description": "fnx.Graph(multigraph_instance) / fnx.DiGraph(multidigraph_instance) returned an empty graph (only nodes copied, edges dropped). nx collapses parallel edges into simple edges with last-parallel-wins attrs. Rust __new__ only handles same-class instances; Python __init__ override in _init_absorbing_dict_of_dicts only handled dict-of-dicts input. Added cross-class multi\u2192simple projection path with correct attrs collapse semantics matching nx. Also covers Multi*\u2192Multi* explicit rebuild so keys survive.", "status": "open", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T04:19:44.934400Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T04:19:44.934400Z", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0}
